99
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:03,960
and keep me company.

100
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:06,960
I don't want to be a burden to anyone.

101
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,200
Who are you meeting?

102
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,400
Your makeup is so exquisite.

103
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,560
Do you remember Ma, the guy I met last time?

104
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,600
He read the fairy tale I wrote before

105
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,680
and liked it a lot.

106
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:31,320
He told me to go to their company today

107
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:32,360
and talk about copyright.

108
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:37,120
Your face is like...

109
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,040
Like what?

110
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,720
Think before you say it.

111
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:44,159
It looks the same as when we were dating.

112
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:51,760
You make yourself look so good.

113
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:52,920
I can't tell

114
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,920
if Ma is interested

115
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:57,600
in your work

116
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,080
or interested in you.

117
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:02,920
Are you being jealous?

118
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,800
If he was interested in me,

119
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,000
you should be secretly happy.

120
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,120
It means that your wife, aka me,

121
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:11,200
is still attractive.

122
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:13,400
What do you mean by still?

123
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,720
You always had it.

124
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:19,160
Good.

125
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,400
You've got some survival instinct,

126
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,240
young lad.

127
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,480
Come on, hurry up.

128
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:26,000
Wish me luck.

129
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:28,960
The breakfast is on the table.

130
00:07:34,159 --> 00:07:35,159
Good morning.

131
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:36,440
Why are you up so early?

132
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:38,159
I could ask you the same question.

133
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,320
I need to go to work.

134
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:40,550
I have clients to meet this morning.

135
00:07:40,550 --> 00:07:41,560
I need to go to work, too.

136
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,180
I need to return to the crew this afternoon.

137
00:07:43,180 --> 00:07:44,000
I have filming to do.

138
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:44,970
Then just wait.

139
00:07:44,970 --> 00:07:45,640
I'll go first.

140
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:46,140
Why?

141
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:47,320
- I'm running out of time. 
 - I'll go first.

142
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,360
- Give me some. 
 - I'll go first.

143
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,560
Come on. Give me.

144
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,960
There you go.

145
00:07:56,320 --> 00:07:57,040
Listen,

146
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,560
I have a lot to do today.

147
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,520
I not only need to go back for filming

148
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:02,600
but have to read the new script.

149
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:11,520
I said I need to read the new script.

150
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:13,600
What's the new script about?

151
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,200
I'll tell you about it later.

152
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,440
Grandma.

153
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:24,640
I'm hungry.

154
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:25,800
Can I have breakfast?

155
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:27,920
Breakfast?

156
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:30,440
It will be lunchtime if you survive 
 another half an hour.

157
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,039
Eat the pills.

158
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:35,039
But I have recovered.

159
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:36,440
Can I stop taking them?

160
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:39,120
As you said, medicine has its side effect.

161
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:41,000
Only the doctor can judge if you have recovered.

162
00:08:41,669 --> 00:08:43,559
Wait until the follow-up checks the day after.

163
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,600
If the doctor says you don't have to take them,

164
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:46,600
you can stop then.

165
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:48,800
But now, you have to take them.

166
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:49,560
OK.

167
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,080
Grandma,

168
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,920
why don't you go and sing these days?

169
00:08:58,560 --> 00:08:59,400
It's getting cold.

170
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,720
We have suspended the activities.

171
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:05,200
It's windy these days, and the temperature will drop.

172
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,880
You're not allowed to go out, too.

173
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,080
I see.

174
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:21,680
How long has it been since you

175
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:22,760
started writing?

176
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,440
Almost three years.

177
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:29,200
Did you

178
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,240
get in contact with other companies before?

179
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,120
Yes, I did.

180
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:34,400
I have a WeChat public account for writing.

181
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,480
Before this, a company

182
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,500
liked the novels I wrote in the public account

183
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:40,080
which are all about different characters.

184
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,960
They wanted to use the stories as short film plots.

185
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:46,240
Have you talked about this fairy tale

186
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:47,880
with any other companies?

187
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:48,760
No.

188
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:50,840
I wasn't planning to write a fairy tale anyway.

189
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:52,200
But,

190
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:53,600
after I had a daughter,

191
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:54,720
she asked me to tell her

192
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,040
bedtime stories every night.

193
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:58,400
You know, just to put her to bed.

194
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,800
I was making up stories.

195
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:01,680
But when it went on,

196
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:04,000
I found out everything was connected

197
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:05,720
and the logic became clearer.

198
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,360
That's why I started writing.

199
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:11,000
But that's how things happen in general.

200
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:14,040
The most precious stories are written

201
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:15,880
when you don't intend it.

202
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:20,120
Many things grow in the gardens

203
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,800
that were never sown there.

204
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:26,320
Right.

205
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:27,320
My colleagues

206
00:10:27,760 --> 00:10:30,400
are in charge of evaluation and I

207
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,330
have read your work.

208
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,240
All of us like it a lot.

209
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:34,080
Thank you.

210
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,400
But I have a proposal.

211
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:37,640
Tell me.

212
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,760
With the material you present me,

213
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:41,960
if we were to publish them,

214
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:43,360
they are too much for one book

215
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:44,600
but not enough for two.

216
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:48,040
My suggestion is

217
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:49,600
to do two things at the same time.

218
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:51,960
On the one hand,

219
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:53,280
finish what you're writing now

220
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:56,640
and make the length of the story enough for two novels.

221
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:58,640
We can immediately publish a set of

222
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:01,520
fairy tales with two volumes

223
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:03,600
with your names on them.

224
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,320
On the other,

225
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:07,080
I have contacted friends

226
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,280
from an internet platform.

227
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,920
Together, we can

228
00:11:09,920 --> 00:11:11,360
record a set of audible books

229
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,720
specifically for kids

230
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,800
as bedtime stories.

231
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:15,880
This way,

232
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:17,560
many parents

233
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:19,240
can save a lot of time.

234
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:22,240
In the future, if the market response is good,

235
00:11:22,560 --> 00:11:25,280
we also plan to make it into an animated cartoon.

236
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:26,880
What do you think?

237
00:11:26,880 --> 00:11:27,720
Sure.

238
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:29,440
Of course, I agree.

239
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:30,960
Good, then.

240
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,120
Here's a contract.

241
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:35,240
The terms are very detailed.

242
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,800
Take it back and have a look.

243
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,760
If you have any questions,

244
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:41,200
contact me anytime.

245
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:41,640
OK.

246
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,360
I'll have a look now.

247
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,360
It's worth a lot.

248
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:03,160
Copyright is the most valuable.

249
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,160
Although the payment is good,

250
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,440
your work pressure

251
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:10,000
will be quite heavy after signing the contract.

252
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:12,720
You can't write only when you have time

253
00:12:12,720 --> 00:12:13,960
just like before.

254
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:16,080
All the clients

255
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:17,760
are waiting for you to deliver something.

256
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:18,680
Rest assured.

257
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:20,920
I will never delay what I promise you.

258
00:12:21,320 --> 00:12:21,920
OK.

259
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:23,360
I look forward

260
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:27,520
to working with you.

261
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:29,400
Me too.

262
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,320
Liu.

263
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:43,600
I'd like to ask you something.

264
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:45,920
When others take a photo,

265
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:47,280
the person is in focus

266
00:13:47,280 --> 00:13:48,840
and the background is blurred.

267
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:50,440
But in my photo,

268
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:52,800
both the person and the background are in focus.

269
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:54,600
What's the reason?

270
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,000
If I guess it right,

271
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,400
you are using a normal lens.

272
00:13:57,560 --> 00:13:58,400
Yeah.

273
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,960
When I bought the camera,

274
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:01,400
it was included in the whole set.

275
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:02,640
If you want to take a portrait,

276
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:04,480
you need to use a medium telephoto lens.

277
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,720
I need to buy a medium telephoto lens.

278
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:10,000
You don't have to buy one.

279
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:10,880
I can gift you one.

280
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,400
That's too kind.

281
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:13,400
How about this?

282
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:14,920
Make me an offer and I'll buy it.

283
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:15,880
It's okay.

284
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:16,730
I have several.

285
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:17,560
Let's do it like this.

286
00:14:17,560 --> 00:14:18,560
When you have time,

287
00:14:18,560 --> 00:14:19,520
come to my studio.

288
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:20,730
I can teach you photography.

289
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:23,000
I'm retired.

290
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,040
I have time every day.

291
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:27,160
How about tomorrow?

