00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:29,360
Tomorrow?

293
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,280
No problem.

294
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:32,240
That's great.

295
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:34,040
After I know how to do it,

296
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:36,080
I can take photos of Mrs. Bai.

297
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,760
Bring her with you.

298
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:39,920
Thank you.

299
00:14:39,920 --> 00:14:41,780
Go to the living room and stay with Liu.

300
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:43,600
It's okay.

301
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:45,280
He and Doctor Lu are chatting happily.

302
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:47,320
I will kill the mood.

303
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:51,000
Grandma,

304
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,480
what do you think of Liu?

305
00:14:53,720 --> 00:14:54,800
What do you mean?

306
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:56,600
He looks really good, right?

307
00:14:58,320 --> 00:15:00,040
But you can't earn a living by good looks.

308
00:15:00,830 --> 00:15:02,440
As long as he treats you well, it's fine.

309
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:03,800
He treats me well indeed.

310
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:06,120
But it's still the probation period.

311
00:15:06,450 --> 00:15:07,800
What's the probation period for?

312
00:15:08,060 --> 00:15:10,600
Even when you buy a television, you have to 
 test the quality.

313
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:12,200
When it's a living person,

314
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,440
you have to be more careful.

315
00:15:14,160 --> 00:15:15,920
You don't want eye candy.

316
00:15:15,920 --> 00:15:17,080
Why are you judging others?

317
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:19,160
You only have good looks left.

318
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:20,440
Exactly.

319
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:22,520
I have more reason to find a practical guy.

320
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:25,280
You're like a criminal suing the victim.

321
00:15:25,560 --> 00:15:26,240
You're in the wrong

322
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:27,840
but defend yourself by sophistry.

323
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:29,440
Tell Liu

324
00:15:29,640 --> 00:15:30,840
not to hurry back.

325
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:32,720
Let's have dinner at home.

326
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,280
I will cook him dinner.

327
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:36,360
I'll make pearl-like glutinous rice and pork balls.

328
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:38,680
I don't need to tell him.

329
00:15:38,840 --> 00:15:39,840
He isn't in a hurry at all.

330
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:40,720
I'll also make

331
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:42,440
Yam pork ribs soup.

332
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:43,640
No.

333
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:46,040
Liu Liangzhou is allergic to yam.

334
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:47,480
What isn't he allergic to?

335
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:51,800
He can't eat

336
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:53,400
lotus root,

337
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,040
okra and anything

338
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:56,040
that is sticky inside.

339
00:15:57,440 --> 00:15:58,360
Alright.

340
00:15:58,720 --> 00:15:59,880
Pork rib soup, then.

341
00:15:59,880 --> 00:16:00,840
I won't add the okra.

342
00:16:01,760 --> 00:16:02,600
Perfect.

343
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,280
I'll thank you for him.

344
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:11,320
What do you think?

345
00:16:11,640 --> 00:16:12,880
Any problems?

346
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,000
Very formal.

347
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:18,720
Very carefully phrased.

348
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:19,760
What else?

349
00:16:21,760 --> 00:16:22,960
Very strict.

350
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:25,920
In what way?

351
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,520
The terms are way too detailed.

352
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:32,360
If you can't accomplish or fulfill

353
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:33,720
any of these,

354
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,800
you might be liable for the breach of the contract.

355
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:37,560
Then it's alright if I don't break the terms, right?

356
00:16:41,760 --> 00:16:44,160
But you need to work very hard in the next few months.

357
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:47,320
I don't mind hard work.

358
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,520
I've thought it through.

359
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:50,400
It's always better early than late.

360
00:16:50,560 --> 00:16:52,000
They give me two months

361
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:52,920
to finish the novel, right?

362
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:54,760
I'm going to finish it in one month.

363
00:16:56,760 --> 00:16:58,320
Then you will have no time at all

364
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,400
to take care of our family.

365
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,360
But didn't you promise me to spend

366
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:04,920
more time taking care of the children

367
00:17:04,920 --> 00:17:06,359
and the family?

368
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:07,720
You regret it, right?

369
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:08,599
No.

370
00:17:09,119 --> 00:17:09,960
I was just saying

371
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:12,640
because you won't have any time for our family,

372
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:14,280
I will do it.

373
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:15,880
No problem.

374
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:17,680
I'm just afraid

375
00:17:19,599 --> 00:17:20,520
that I am

376
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:21,319
a clumsy person.

377
00:17:21,319 --> 00:17:22,800
You're not clumsy.

378
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:25,200
Don't overestimate me.

379
00:17:26,319 --> 00:17:27,880
I've been thinking.

380
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:30,040
How about

381
00:17:30,040 --> 00:17:31,440
we hire a nanny?

382
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:32,120
What do you think?

383
00:17:32,360 --> 00:17:33,200
Don't.

384
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:36,720
Nannies can't be as devoted to the children as the dad.

385
00:17:36,840 --> 00:17:38,800
I knew you'd be waiting to say this.

386
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,240
Tell me the truth.

387
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:48,120
Were you startled to see my royalties?

388
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,840
In the end, writers like you are the best.

389
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:53,880
You can just be idle.

390
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:55,080
But once you start working,

391
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,560
others will envy you.

392
00:17:58,320 --> 00:18:00,000
Just tell me, am I good?

393
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:02,320
In the future,

394
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:03,880
you don't have to go to work.

395
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:05,960
I will write and provide for you,

396
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:07,560
OK.

397
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,240
You're really good.

398
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:13,240
After finishing this book,

399
00:18:13,240 --> 00:18:14,320
I'll write a new one.

400
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:15,760
I have already named it.

401
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:18,680
It's called Forcing My Husband to Be A Toy Boy.

402
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:20,440
I'll write one too.

403
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:22,880
I'll call it Proudly Being a Toy Boy.

404
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:55,320
One, two, three, four.

405
00:19:01,560 --> 00:19:02,560
I want to try, too.

406
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:03,840
Here.

407
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:12,800
One, two, three, four.

408
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:15,440
Come on.

409
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:23,640
One, two, three, four.

410
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:27,840
Good.

411
00:19:28,720 --> 00:19:29,600
Shake it evenly.

412
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:31,320
Use the same strength back and forth.

413
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:34,640
One, two, three, four.

414
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:35,400
Good.

415
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:41,480
I haven't seen you so excited for many years.

416
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:44,080
Your birthday is approaching.

417
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:46,080
But you know that I never celebrate birthdays.

418
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:47,840
Let's celebrate it this time.

419
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:50,280
What for?

420
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:52,560
I just want to celebrate it for you.

421
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:59,000
Look at me.

422
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,720
Is there something wrong?

423
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:04,040
What could possibly go wrong?

424
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:05,200
I'm alright.

425
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:07,200
What medicine did you take?

426
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:11,720
The supplements you bought me.

427
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,160
Look. The supplements.

428
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:16,980
I didn't lie to you.

429
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:25,200
But we agreed

430
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:27,010
that we won't keep anything from each other.

431
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:28,800
You're so suspicious.

432
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,160
I'm not keeping anything from you.

433
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:35,640
[Crossroad Bistro]

434
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:45,200
Let's go.

435
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,080
It's windy outside and must be really cold.

436
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:49,440
Listen to me and take a taxi.

437
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:50,560
I'll ride the motorcycle alone.

438
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:52,200
Aren't you cold?

439
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:54,800
I'm used to it.

440
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,320
No.

441
00:20:56,320 --> 00:20:57,800
We are a family, right?

442
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,760
We have to share joys and sorrows.

443
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:01,840
What about we both take the taxi?

444
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:04,200
It's not safe to leave the motorcycle here all night.

445
00:21:04,720 --> 00:21:06,640
Be good. Take the taxi.

446
00:21:08,160 --> 00:21:09,240
No.

447
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:13,040
Alright, then.

448
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:30,160
Hop up.

449
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:35,440
Hug me tight and you won't be cold.

450
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:10,920
Why are you still awake?

451
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:12,440
I'm not sleepy yet.

452
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:13,320
Go to bed first.

453
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:18,760
I'll pour more water for you.

454
00:22:22,030 --> 00:22:23,640
Why are you drinking coffee at this time?

455
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:25,520
You don't plan to sleep tonight, do you?

456
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:27,040
Go to bed first.

457
00:22:27,040 --> 00:22:29,120
I'm fired with creative inspiration.

458
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:30,640
My proverbial juice is starting to flow.

459
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:36,720
Don't be too tired.

460
00:22:43,650 --> 00:22:44,600
Hurry up and get inside.

461
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:45,520
I'm so cold.

462
00:22:58,760 --> 00:22:59,880
You're frozen.

463
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:01,800
My face is numb thanks to the wind.

464
00:23:02,840 --> 00:23:03,840
Do nothing else

465
00:23:03,840 --> 00:23:05,160
and take a hot shower now.

466
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:06,040
Be good.

467
00:23:43,840 --> 00:23:45,160
Don't tell me you haven't slept.

468
00:23:46,480 --> 00:23:47,360
I'm sleepy.

469
00:23:47,830 --> 00:23:49,280
I don't have the strength to write.

470
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:55,840
Good job.

471
00:23:58,000 --> 00:23:59,920
You work too hard.

472
00:24:00,310 --> 00:24:02,200
I'll take the children to school later on.

473
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:05,000
But you need to pick them up for me today.

474
00:24:06,640 --> 00:24:08,880
I need to go to the client's place this afternoon.

475
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:10,200
I will get back

476
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:12,320
after dinner, more or less.

477
00:24:19,640 --> 00:24:21,760
Get undressed and sleep comfortably.

478
00:24:23,120 --> 00:24:24,040
Beautiful.

479
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:28,700
♫I will grow old eventually♫

480
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:27,440
How about this?

481
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:28,880
Your head is too high.

482
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:29,720
Tuck your chin in a bit.

483
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:32,400
♫I think about our love♫

484
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:32,160
Liu.

485
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:36,060
♫Every day♫

486
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:34,360
Will Mrs. Bai look better

487
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:36,760
if I take the photo from a higher

488
00:24:36,760 --> 00:24:38,240
or lower position?

489
00:24:38,240 --> 00:24:41,120
I think it should be a bit lower than before.

490
00:24:39,170 --> 00:24:42,790
♫I want to beg for more time♫

491
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:41,960
A bit lower, right?

492
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:42,440
Yes.

493
00:24:42,440 --> 00:24:43,280
Alright.

494
00:24:43,040 --> 00:24:45,230
♫So that I can♫

495
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:46,480
Doctor Lu.

496
00:24:45,510 --> 00:24:47,530
♫Stay with you♫

497
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:47,640
You don't have to do that.

498
00:24:47,830 --> 00:24:49,620
♫But I have♫

499
00:24:48,490 --> 00:24:50,390
This angle is too low in portrait photography.

500
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:53,340
♫Run out of my luck♫

501
00:24:50,390 --> 00:24:50,920
It's too much.

502
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:51,480
There's no need.

503
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:52,640
Don't break the camera.

504
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:53,960
Just do it normally.

505
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:55,120
Right.

506
00:24:54,840 --> 00:24:56,400
♫We are♫

507
00:24:56,480 --> 00:24:58,280
Here's a flying one.

508
00:24:57,080 --> 00:25:00,370
♫Who we are♫

509
00:24:58,560 --> 00:24:59,480
What do you think, Liu?

510
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:00,840
This one is so good.

511
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:01,680
Can I see it?

512
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:02,920
Yes.

513
00:25:01,770 --> 00:25:04,740
♫We're there for each other in laughter and tears♫

514
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:06,480
Mrs. Bai, you look so good on camera.

515
00:25:05,260 --> 00:25:07,820
♫We are by each other's side♫

516
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:08,200
This one?

517
00:25:08,260 --> 00:25:11,200
♫We will stay together♫

518
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:09,400
Looks good!

519
00:25:11,520 --> 00:25:13,000
The camera is good.

520
00:25:11,830 --> 00:25:15,370
♫And fight till the end of time♫

521
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:13,840
No.

522
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:15,880
You look good.

523
00:25:16,290 --> 00:25:18,420
♫Little did we know that in front of life♫

524
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:20,800
I didn't even think I'd take such a good photo.

525
00:25:18,590 --> 00:25:20,530
♫We♫

526
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:23,120
It looks great.

527
00:25:23,640 --> 00:25:24,240
Liu.

528
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:27,600
♫We don't stand a chance♫

529
00:25:24,560 --> 00:25:26,160
Mrs. Bai

530
00:25:27,120 --> 00:25:28,440
deserves

531
00:25:28,440 --> 00:25:29,560
such a great camera.

532
00:25:28,820 --> 00:25:31,880
♫Don't leave me. Don't miss me♫

533
00:25:30,400 --> 00:25:31,120
The camera's good.

534
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:32,000
The lenses are nice, too.

535
00:25:32,360 --> 00:25:34,680
But people are vital in photography.

536
00:25:32,380 --> 00:25:35,190
♫Things aren't always what they're supposed to be♫

537
00:25:35,520 --> 00:25:37,800
The photographer and the model need to connect

538
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:38,940
♫Don't talk to me. We all make compromises♫

539
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,600
to achieve a good photo.

540
00:25:41,340 --> 00:25:46,290
♫We are on the crossroad♫

541
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:42,240
You see?

542
00:25:42,240 --> 00:25:43,440
Dr. Lu, believe it or not.

543
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:45,440
If the model is Xiaoyu, I'll do a better job than you.

544
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:46,200
Of course.

545
00:25:46,600 --> 00:25:47,400
It's the same.

546
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:48,400
If I take a photo of Mrs. Bai,

547
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:49,720
